{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01QRWZX98wZiYFwD7oM7DgVM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is restored. \n\n## Summary\n\n**Diagnosis:** The `elasticsearch` namespace held two StatefulSets:\n- `es-alpha` — the intended 3-node production cluster.\n- `es-beta` — a separate 1-node StatefulSet whose ConfigMap (`es-beta-config`) was misconfigured with `cluster.name: es-alpha` and `discovery.seed_hosts` pointing at es-alpha. As a result `es-beta-0` joined `es-alpha` as a **4th, master-eligible node**.\n\nSo the cluster was not in its expected clean 3-node state, and the extra master-eligible node created split-brain risk. (No NetworkPolicies were present; the issue was purely the rogue node.)\n\n**Fix:** Scaled `es-beta` down to 0 replicas, removing the misconfigured node from the `es-alpha` cluster. This is minimal and reversible — `es-beta` couldn't function as its own cluster anyway (its config lacked `cluster.initial_master_nodes`), confirming it was never meant to be a standalone cluster. No operators or CRDs were touched.\n\n**Verified end state — `es-alpha` cluster:**\n- `status: green`\n- `number_of_nodes: 3` / `number_of_data_nodes: 3` (es-alpha-0/1/2)\n- `active_shards_percent: 100.0`, `unassigned_shards: 0`\n\nThe replica that had lived on es-beta-0 was automatically reallocated to the three remaining nodes, bringing the cluster back to green."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":878,"cache_read_input_tokens":39796,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":878},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3aedd27f-e71d-4edf-b550-5c33e323e8ed","uuid":"d4b4c4c4-8b51-4d70-a2e1-fcbe042807fb","request_id":"req_011CcAhnFWXqSCkGCUrnL1DS"}
